HEADWORD: Pampre
<hw>Pam"pre</hw> <pr>(p⟦acr⟧m"p⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>pampre</ets> a vine branch, L. <ets>pampinus</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Sculp.)</fld> <def>An ornament, composed of vine leaves and
bunches of grapes, used for decorating spiral columns.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pamprodactylous</ent>⟦br⟧
